BELLABEAT¶

Urška Sršen and Sando Mur founded Bellabeat, a high-tech company that manufactures health-focused smart products. Sršen used her background as an artist to develop beautifully designed technology that informs and inspires women around the world. Collecting data on activity, sleep, stress, and reproductive health has allowed Bellabeat to empower women with knowledge about their own health and habits. Since it was founded in 2013, Bellabeat has grown rapidly and quickly positioned itself as a tech-driven wellness company for women. By 2016, Bellabeat had opened offices around the world and launched multiple products. Bellabeat products became available through a growing number of online retailers in addition to their own e-commerce channel on their website. The company has invested in traditional advertising media, such as radio, out-of-home billboards, print, and television, but focuses on digital marketing extensively. Bellabeat invests year-round in Google Search, maintaining active Facebook and Instagram pages, and consistently engages consumers on Twitter. Additionally, Bellabeat runs video ads on Youtube and display ads on the Google Display Network to support campaigns around key marketing dates.¶

Project Background¶

Bellabeat is a high tech smart device company focuses on women.¶

Their product track¶

  • Physical activities
  • Sleep pattern
  • Heart rate & etc.

ASK¶

Objective¶

Grown and become a larger player in the smart device industry.

Main tasks¶

  • Identify the trends on usage
  • Use trends to influence Bellabeat marketing strategy

Stakeholders¶

  • Urška Sršen: Bellabeat’s cofounder and Chief Creative Officer
  • Sando Mur: Mathematician and Bellabeat’s cofounder; key member of the Bellabeat executive team
  • Bellabeat marketing analytics team: A team of data analysts responsible for collecting, analyzing, and reporting data that helps guide Bellabeat’s marketing strategy.

PREPARE¶

Data source¶

  • The data which we are working on right now is not bellabeat's data it is an open-source data available on kaggle named 'FitBit Fitness Tracker Data'.
  • It is consist of 18 csv files.
  • FitBit users consented to the submission of personal tracker data.

Limitation of the dataset¶

  • The data is collected in 2016, 6 years ago. Data may not be relevant to today's time.
  • The data have very low sample size, consist of only 30 users.

Data credibility¶

  • Reliable- Not reliable as it have only 30 users data.
  • Original- Third party providor.
  • Current- The data was taken in 2016, not current.
  • Cited- As the data is collected from the third party, hence unknown.

Tools¶

The tools we are going to use for this analysis is python for data cleaning, processing, transformation and visualization.

In [14]:
#Daily, Hourly & Sleepday have Date data in Object Datatypes
#So we will convert that dtype into datatime dtype
daily_data["ActivityDate"]=pd.to_datetime(daily_data["ActivityDate"])
hourlyI_data["ActivityHour"]=pd.to_datetime(hourlyI_data["ActivityHour"])
sleepday_data["SleepDay"]=pd.to_datetime(sleepday_data["SleepDay"])
In [15]:
daily_data["WeekDay"]=daily_data["ActivityDate"].dt.day_name()
hourlyI_data["WeekDay"]=hourlyI_data["ActivityHour"].dt.day_name()
sleepday_data["WeekDay"]=sleepday_data["SleepDay"].dt.day_name()

Summary of last few steps in Process. We joined all the hourly data in one one hourly dataframe 'hourlyI_data' dataframe. We converted object datatype into datetime datatype.

Findings:¶

  • The CDC recommend that most adults aim for 10,000 steps per day and comparing this with our findings the users lack almost 2500 steps in their daily goals.
  • For most people,the equivalent distance covered is about 8 kilometers, or 5 miles and user still lacks almost 2.5 kilometers on the daily basis.
  • According to the Dietary Guidelines for Americans 2020–2025, the average adult woman expends roughly 1,600 to 2,400 calories per day.

ACT¶

Recommendation:¶

  • We can promote users by setting a goal of 10,000 steps per day will help them stay healthy.
  • As 81% of users spend most of their time sitting, we can provide some type of exercise to make them a little bit more active.
  • By seeing the graphs, most of the users sleeps better in weekends.
